title: Saints' Mogren Earns Weekly UMAC Honor
text:
Saints' Mogren Earns Weekly UMAC Honor 
By Zach Schneider Saints' Mogren Earns Weekly UMAC Honor October 20, 2015 Updated Oct 20, 2015 at 12:41 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- St. Scholastica's Andrea Mogren has been named the Upper Midwest Athletic Conference (UMAC) women's cross country runner of the week, it was announced on Tuesday afternoon. 
Mogren led the Saints at the NCAA Preview race in Oshkosh, Wis. this past weekend, finishing with a personal-best time of 22:41 to finish in 65th place.
